node.text: Short film by @taylorglenn | We all know people whose dedication to a passion or purpose inspires us deeply. Gannett Horn's (@surfasaur) focus on his sport and love for its community embodies the best in each of us. This short film is a testament to Gannett and those who motivate us to work harder at the things we love. #riversurfing Production by @apresvisuals

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Adventure on July 23, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Photo by @jason_gulley_science / Cave explorer Annelie Bergstrom probes a cave passage deep inside the Matanuska Glacier during my third research expedition to Alaska, in 2007. I spent several field seasons camped on the Matanuska, exploring and mapping glacier caves as part of my Ph.D. research into how glacier caves form and affect glacier motion. Because I had very limited funding, the road-accessible Matanuska Glacier was an ideal research site because there was no need to charter aircraft for access. #Alaska #glacier #cave #glaciercave #science

node.text: Photos by @donaldmiralle / A selection of images from the previous Summer Olympics I’ve photographed. For the next 16 days I’ll be covering my 10th Olympics, with 28 sports with over 11,000 athletes from more than 207 countries represented. I have a love/hate relationship with the Olympics, as no sporting event is as exciting nor as exhausting as a photographer. Feel free to follow my Olympic journey here and at @natgeointhefield
